At timestep t t , the controller maintains a structured runtime state: s t = { x 1 : t , z t , P t , H t , c t , D t , F t , κ t } s_{t}=\{x_{1:t},z_{t},P_{t},H_{t},c_{t},D_{t},F_{t},\kappa_{t}\}

where: • x 1 : t x_{1:t} : generated token sequence • z t z_{t} : raw logits • P t P_{t} : top- k k token distribution • H t H_{t} : entropy of P t P_{t} • c t c_{t} : contract progress (stage and metadata) • D t ∈ [ 0 , 1 ] D_{t}\in[0,1] : heuristic drift score • F t ∈ [ 0 , 1 ] F_{t}\in[0,1] : learned failure probability • κ t \kappa_{t} : number of corrections applied

This explicit state representation enables the controller to reason about both structural progress and trajectory-level uncertainty.
